summary: I think the reason the Pokémon detective pikachu works with the "realistic" animation are a few things, there plenty of...
body:
I think the reason the Pokémon detective pikachu works with the “realistic” animation are a few things, there plenty of traditional animation and there will be no doubt more. There monsters that aren’t real so it’s interesting to see how they would be in real life and lastly and I think most important is that it isn’t really realistic.

This is the movie, sure the textures are real but those eyes for one are way too big for a creature that size and there are other things.

Source

This is realistic the eyes, feet, nose and much more are so much more real feeling but which one would you rather want to have a whole movie about? (The art is great and the artist did an amazing job but the movie’s pikachu looks more fun and expressive )

Anyway I don’t know what my point is but I had this random thought and wanted to share.

summary: Ok this gonna sound ridiculous but just listen: Does anyone else feel like eevee’s head in the Detective Pikachu casting call...
body:
Ok this gonna sound ridiculous but just listen:

Does anyone else feel like eevee’s head in the Detective Pikachu casting call thing is too round?

I’m not trying to call it ugly, whatever, it’s still cute, just not the typical eevee brand of cute.

It’s just that compared to every other version of eevee I’ve seen through games, comics, animes, and fanworks, that head is round, and the ears look a little far apart, possibly because of the roundness. Or maybe the roundness is accentuated by how apart the ears are? idk.

Sure some pokemon have some slight cosmetic changes for the sake of giving them that realism but this doesn’t really feel like that, and it just kind of nudges eevee too close to sort of uncanny valley feeling. Eevee’s have an eevee shape and so much about the DP eevee mostly matches it, except for the head, and that knowledge tugs at my consciousness each time I see it.

summary: I think Disney also keeps messing up because like we got a new Detective Pikachu trailer that looks way better than the Lion...
body:
I think Disney also keeps messing up because like we got a new Detective Pikachu trailer that looks way better than the Lion King trailer. Not only do the Pokemon look realistic and still look like their animated counterparts, but the trailer is also full of color.

When I search for pictures of the African plains, this is what I get:

It’s full of color, it looks full of life. But the scenes from the Lion King trailer? Everything looks dull. Yes, I know some of the scenes are from the wildebeest stampede but after that, everything still looks so lackluster. Africa isn’t grey, it’s vibrant!
